text: Bill Proctor is the Leon County, Florida District 1 County Commissioner, a role in which he has served since 1996. He has also been an Instructor Political Science at Florida A&M University in Tallahassee, Florida since August 2000. Previously, he served on former Florida Governor Lawton Chiles' 1994 re-election committee before being essentially fired according to Chuck Wolfe, Chiles' director of external affairs.

Sayyed As'ad Madani (April 27, 1928 AD-February 6, 2006 AD) (Urdu: سید اسعد مدنے ) was an Indian Deobandi Islamic scholar and politician. He was the President of Jamiat Ulema-e-Hind and a prominent member of executive body (Majlis-e-Shura) of Darul Uloom Deoband.
